    <para id="id45283824">The region of convergence (ROC) of 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mtext>~</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>z</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ {X}  cSup { size 8{ "~" } }  \( z \) } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is |z| &gt; |a|, i.e., outside a circle of radius a.</para>
