    <list id="id45432943" list-type="bulleted">
      <item>Causal sequences have ROCs outside a circle that intersects the pole.</item>
      <item>Anti-causal sequences have ROCs inside a circle that intersects the pole.</item>
      <item>Bounded sequences have ROCs that include the unit circle.</item>
      <item>Unbounded sequences have ROCs that do not include the unit circle.</item>
    </list>
    <para id="id45398057">7/ Two-sided DT time function</para>
    <para id="id45398064">Next we consider the two-sided sequence</para>
    <para id="id45398068">
