    <para id="id45485573">Note that, the delayed sequence has the same ROC as the original sequence.</para>
    <para id="id45485579">III. CONCLUSIONS</para>
    <para id="id45485583">The Z-transform is capable of representing a rich class of DT time functions. Z-transform pairs can be obtained by combining</para>
    <list id="id45485590" list-type="bulleted">
      <item>Z-transform properties.</item>
      <item>the Z-transforms of elementary time functions.</item>
